      <byline class="print_byline">By Stuart Elliott</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Elliott, Stuart</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Seagate Technology Inc awards its corporate brand agency, Foote, Cone &amp; Belding, added duties for disk drive and tape drive products; account had been handled by van Bronkhorst Group; Mastercard International Inc awards its Internet advertising account to GSD&amp;M; account had been handled by Thunderhouse (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>* Seagate Technology Inc., Scotts Valley, Calif., expanded its relationship with its corporate brand agency, Foote, Cone &amp; Belding, San Francisco, part of True North Communications, by awarding the agency additional duties for disk drive and tape drive products. That account, with estimated billings of $12 million, had been handled by van Bronkhorst Group, Santa Clara, Calif.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>* Seagate Technology Inc., Scotts Valley, Calif., expanded its relationship with its corporate brand agency, Foote, Cone &amp; Belding, San Francisco, part of True North Communications, by awarding the agency additional duties for disk drive and tape drive products. That account, with estimated billings of $12 million, had been handled by van Bronkhorst Group, Santa Clara, Calif.</p>
        <p>* Mastercard International Inc., Purchase, N.Y., to GSD&amp; M, Austin, Tex., a unit of Omnicom Group, to handle its Internet advertising, which had been handled by Thunderhouse, a division of McCann-Erickson World Group, New York, part of the Interpublic Group of Cos. Billings were estimated at $5 million. GSD&amp; M already handles media services for Mastercard.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
